      "updated": "2021-02-19 04:24:54.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "c707d30d_8e65168e",
      "file_path": "cps-nf-proxy-rest/src/main/resources/changelog/changelog-master.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 5,
      "message": "I'm suggesting prefixing change files with 2 or 3 digits (01-..., 02-...) to keep the files sorted in the folder. Later on, this will prevent mixing old and new files together and make them much more convenient to work with.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-19 04:24:54.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "9c172171_724f777f",
      "file_path": "cps-nf-proxy-rest/src/main/resources/changelog/db/changes/1-dataspace.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 7,
      "message": "I'm missing the reason for this precondition on the existence of the table and the warning.\n\nI presume that if the table does not exist, the script will not be able to load the data and is expecting to fail anyway.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-19 04:24:54.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "5a359f19_9aa55e13",
      "file_path": "cps-nf-proxy-rest/src/main/resources/changelog/db/changes/1-dataspace.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 14,
      "message": "Is there any risk that the script unexpectedly updates and erase any data is already in the database ?\n\nIf we know for sure that the script only needs to be run for the first time when the table is empty we could have a precondition like:\n\n```\n<preConditions>\n  <sqlCheck expectedResult=\"0\">\n    SELECT COUNT(1) FROM pg_tables WHERE TABLENAME = 'myRequiredTable'\n  </sqlCheck>\n</preConditions>\n```\n\nToine, maybe you can precise the use case to come with appropriate script controls.\n\nOne more thing, we are not supposed to provide the id in the change set as this is a database responsibility (auto generated by sequences). We need to be careful, it can lead to inconsistencies.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-19 04:24:54.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
